bill france jr  wikipedia bill france jr from wikipedia the free encyclopedia   redirected from bill france jr jump to navigation search bill france jr born william clifton france april   washington dc died june   aged  daytona beach fl cause of death lung cancer resting place daytona memorial park alma mater university of florida known for served as head of nascar from  to  spouses betty jane children brian lesa parents bill france sr anne bledsoe william clifton bill france april    june   nicknamed bill france jr or little billy was an american motorsports executive who served from  to  as the chief executive officer ceo of nascar the sanctioning body of the usbased stock car racing he succeeded his father nascar founder bill france sr as its ceo his son brian france has been ceo since  contents  early life  career  later life  halls of fame inductions  references  further reading  external links early lifeedit france was born in washington dc to anne bledsoe and william henry getty france his family moved to daytona beach florida in  to escape the great depression he attended seabreeze high school before attending the university of florida he served for two years in the united states navy before turning to a career in racing france grew up helping at race tracks he sold concessions and helped park cars at the daytona beach road course he worked twelve hours per day seven days a week for thirteen months with the construction of daytona international speedway where he drove a compactor bulldozer and grader he once tried using a mule to pull trees out of the swamp because motorized equipment was getting stuck he rode offroad motorcycles and began competing in enduros in the s france entered the baja  in the motorcycle division in the early s he gave the upandcoming sport of motocross a chance at daytona in the early s the motocross races started with little fanfare but grew into the popular daytona supercross the supercross inspired the daytona beach bike week careeredit after serving as vicepresident for six years he became the head of nascar when his father bill france sr retired on january   the international motorsports hall of fame describes the transition other than the founding of nascar itself bill jrs appointment to leadership is probably the most significant event in the history of the sanctioning body  nascar went from a southern regional sport to a national sport during his tenure france jr was instrumental in taking the sport outside of its traditional american base in  he struck a deal with multimilliondollar australian tire retailer and retired racer bob jane to take stock car racing to australia and plans were laid out for a highbanked speedway at the jane owned calder park raceway in melbourne the  mi  km calder park thunderdome the first highbanked nascar style speedway built outside of north america was built at a cost of a million and was opened in  the new track modelled on a scaled down version of the charlotte motor speedway including mimicking its ° banked turns held its first nascar race the goodyear nascar  for  km on february   and was won by alabama gang member neil bonnet driving a pontiac grand prix although only an exhibition race this was also the first nascar race held outside of north america jane became the head of the sanctioning body for stock car racing in australia known as australian stock car auto racing auscar though a falling out between him and france in  saw nascar withdraw its support for jane and his track nascar racing in australia continued to be sanctioned by jane until the series folded in  he continued his fathers legacy by fostering growth of the daytona  stock car race and daytona  motorcycle race at daytona international speedway the winston million program was launched by rj reynolds in  a  million bonus was awarded to any driver who could win three of four preselected racescitation needed nascars grand national series was renamed winston cup now monster energy cup in  the points fund increased from  to  million the champions portion of the points fund rose to  million by  nascar had few televised races in  those races that did air in the s were mixed into shows like abc wide world of sports france signed a deal with cbs sports president neal pilson to televise the  daytona  from flag to flag the race was the first live flag to flag national coverage of a nascar race the race got high television ratings partly due to a snowstorm in the midwest and northeast richard petty won the race after race leaders donnie allison and cale yarborough crashed together on the final lap allisons brother bobby allison stopped and bobby allison and yarborough then exchanged punches the ratings and ensuing press coverage helped france to sign television contracts with espn in  tnn in  and tbs frances career culminated in a recordsetting  billion television broadcasting contract in  for the  season france was a delegate from florida to the  democratic national convention and supported the candidacy of george wallace who had won the florida democratic presidential preference primary that yearcitation needed in  frances employees told him about sixyearold ohio leukemia patient sarah ashley secoy he called her father and pledged to make her struggle and international marrow donor search a global news story his efforts made her a radio and tv news story he also helped fund sarahs song a duet recorded with her father that france promoted to tens of thousands of radio stations globally millions were thus raised to pay for her sixyear hospital fight inside a germ free chamber her genetic match donor was found she became the first patient ever to survive acute myeloid leukemia thus leading to an all new global treatment concept for several deadly childhood cancers that has now saved thousands of childrens livescitation needed later lifeedit france turned the presidency of nascar over to mike helton in  after being diagnosed with cancer he made his son brian france the ceo and chairman of nascar in  bill france jr remained a member of the sixperson nascar board of directors the france family continues to own nascar outright and has a controlling interest in race track operator international speedway corporation france jr continued as chairman of the board of isc until his death his daughter lesa france kennedy is iscs president france died of lung cancer in daytona beach florida on june   at about  pm his death occurred during the raindelayed autism speaks  cup race and his death was reported during the live broadcast of the race at lap  nascar on fox lead announcer mike joy held a moment of silence during a restart around lap  and the tracks flag was lowered to half staff halls of fame inductionsedit international motorsports hall of fame in  motorcycle hall of fame in  motorsports hall of fame of america in  automotive hall of fame in  nascar hall of fame in  referencesedit  bill fleischman and al pearce the unauthorized nascar fan guide  visible ink press farmington hills michigan usa isbn   a b biography archived september   at the wayback machine at the stock car racing hall of fame of oceanside rotary club  a b c biography at the motorcycle hall of fame archived december   at the wayback machine  a b c d biography at the international motorsports hall of fame archived may   at the wayback machine  biography at findarticlescom  a b biography at the motorsports hall of fame of america archived september   at the wayback machine  espn longtime nascar chairman france jr dies june    automotive hall of fame biography further readingedit timeline bill france jr at nascarcom retrieved june   external linksedit nascar the france family aug    international speedway corporation blake ben a natural progression archived from the original on nov    nascars top job stays in france family espn sep    litsky frank june   bill france jr  dies gave nascar its national reach obituary ny times  bill france jr at find a grave v t e the