r day seven days a week for thirteen months with the construction of daytona international speedway where he drove a compactor bulldozer and grader he once tried using a mule to pull trees out of the swamp because motorized equipment was getting stuck he rode offroad motorcycles and began competing in enduros in the s france entered the baja  in the motorcycle division in the early s he gave the upandcoming sport of motocross a chance at daytona in the early s the motocross races started with little fanfare but grew into the popular daytona supercross the supercross inspired the daytona beach bike week careeredit after serving as vicepresident for six years he became the head of nascar when his father bill france sr retired on january   the international motorsports hall of fame describes the transition other than the founding of nascar itself bill jrs appointment to leadership is probably the most significant event in the history of the sanctioning body  nascar went from a southern regional sport to a national sport during his tenure france jr was instrumental in taking the sport outside of its traditional american base in  he struck a deal with multimilliondollar australian tire retailer and retired racer bob jane to take stock car racing to australia and plans were laid out for a highbanked speedway at the jane owned calder park raceway in melbourne the  mi  km calder park thunderdome the first highbanked nascar style speedway built outside of north america was built at a cost of a million and was opened in  the new track modelled on a scaled down version of the charlotte motor speedway including mimicking its ° banked turns held its first nascar race the goodyear nascar  for  km on february   and was won by alabama gang member neil bonnet driving a pontiac grand prix although only an exhibition race this was also the first nascar race held outside of north america jane became the head of the sanctioning body for stock car racing in australia known as australian stock car auto racing auscar though a falling out between him and france in  saw nascar withdraw its support for jane and his track nascar racing in australia continued to be sanctioned by jane until the series folded in  he continued his fathers legacy by fostering growth of the daytona  stock car race and daytona  motorcycle race at daytona international speedway the winston million program was launched by rj reynolds in  a  million bonus was awarded to any driver who could win three of four preselected racescitation needed nascars grand national series was renamed winston cup now monster energy cup in  the points fund increased from  to  million the champions portion of the points fund rose to  million by  nascar had few televised races in  those races that did air in the s were mixed into shows like abc wide world of sports france signed a deal with cbs sports president neal pilson to televise the  daytona  from flag to flag the race was the first live flag to flag national coverage of a nascar race the race got high television ratings partly due to a snowstorm in the midwest and northeast richard petty won the race after race leaders donnie allison and cale yarborough crashed together on the final lap allisons brother bobby allison stopped and bobby allison and yarborough then exchanged punches the ratings and ensuing press coverage helped france to sign television contracts with espn in  tnn in  and tbs frances career culminated in a recordsetting  billion television broadcasting contract in  for the  season france was a delegate from florida to the  democratic national convention and supported the candidacy of george wallace who had won the florida democratic presidential preference primary that yearcitation needed in  frances employees told him about sixyearold ohio leukemia patient sarah ashley secoy he called her father and pledged to make her struggle and international marrow donor search a global news story his efforts made her a radio and tv news story he also helped fund sarahs song a duet recorded with her father that france promoted to tens of thousands of radio stations globally millions were thus raised to pay for her sixyear hospital fight inside a germ free chamber her genetic match donor was found she became the first patient ever to survive acute myeloid leukemia thus leading to an all new global treatment concept for several deadly childhood cancers that has now saved thousands of childrens livescitation needed later lifeedit france turned the presidency of nascar over to mike helton in  after being diagnosed with cancer he made his son brian france the ceo and chairman of nascar in  bill france jr remained a member of the sixperson nascar board of directors the france family continues to own nascar outright and has a controlling interest in race track operator international speedway corporation france jr continued as chairman of the board of isc until his death his daughter lesa france kennedy is iscs president france died of lung cancer in daytona beach florida on june   at about  pm his death occurred during the raindelayed autism speaks  cup race and his death was reported during the live broadcast of the race at lap  nascar on fox lead announcer mike joy held a moment of silence during a restart around lap  and the tracks flag was lowered to half staff halls of fame inductionsedit international motorsports hall of fame in  motorcycle hall of fame in  motorsports hall of fame of america in  automotive hall of fame in  nascar hall of fame in  referencesedit  bill fleischman and al pearce the unauthorized nascar fan guide  visible ink press farmington hills michigan usa isbn   a b biography archived september   at the wayback machine at the stock car racing hall of fame of oceanside rotary club  a b c biography at the motorcycle hall of fame archived december   at the wayback machine  a b c d biography at the international motorsports hall of fame archived may   at the wayback machine  biography at findarticlescom  a b biography at the motorsports hall of fame of america archived september   at the wayback machine  espn longtime nascar chairman france jr dies june    automotive hall of fame biography further readingedit timeline bill france jr at nascarcom retrieved june   external linksedit nascar the france family aug    international speedway corporation blake ben a natural progression archived from the original on nov    nascars top job stays in france family espn sep    litsky frank june   bill france jr  dies gave nascar its national reach obituary ny times  bill france jr at find a grave v t e the france family of nascar first generation bill france sr second generation bill france jr jim france third generation brian france lesa kennedy j c france fourth generation ben kennedy v t e nascar chairmen and presidents bill france sr bill france jr mike helton brian france major national racing series monster energy nascar cup series daytona  xfinity series camping world truck series regional  local racing series kn pro series east west whelen modified whelen modified tour whelen southern modified tour weekly short track racing whelen allamerican series international series nascar australia nascar in australia auscar nascar canada pintys series nascar europe whelen euro series nascar mexico peak mexico series online racing series nascar iracing series nascar iracingcom series nascar peak antifreeze series former series autozone elite division midwest series northwest series southeast series southwest series other series baby grand national  dash series busch allstar tour convertible division grand american grand national east mini stocks speedway division special events toyota allstar showdown unoh battle at the beach television and radio cbs espnabc foxfox sports  hot pass indycar radio network motor racing network nbcnbcsn performance racing network speed tnt lists drivers female drivers fatalities champions cup series xfinity series champions truck series cu